Join the Group
===

We are always looking for **motivated and talented researchers** to join our group at the **[School of Data Science (SDS)](https://sds.cuhk.edu.cn)**, **[The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shenzhen (CUHK-Shenzhen)](https://www.cuhk.edu.cn/en)**.

Our group conducts research at the intersection of **optimization**, **machine learning**, and **scientific computing**, with current focuses on:

- Optimization theory and algorithmic acceleration  
- AI for Science and data-driven modeling of physical systems  
- Decentralized and distributed algorithms  

If you are passionate about mathematical foundations and algorithmic innovations for AI, we welcome your application.

---

## 🧑‍🎓 PhD Students

We recruit PhD students through the **School of Data Science** PhD program at CUHK-Shenzhen. Applicants should have a strong background in **mathematics**, **computer science**, or **related disciplines**,  with solid analytical skills and research motivation.

### Admission routes

If you are interested, please email me with the subject line **“PhD Application – [Your Name]”**,  
and include the following materials:
- CV / Resume  
- Transcript(s)  
- A brief statement of research interests  
- Publications or project reports (if any)

---

## 🧑‍🔬 Postdoctoral Researchers

We welcome postdoctoral researchers with a strong background in **optimization**, **machine learning**,  **numerical analysis**, or **scientific computing**.  

Interested applicants are encouraged to contact me directly with:
- CV (including publication list)  
- Two representative papers  
- A short research statement outlining future plans  

---

## 🌏 Visiting Students & Research Interns

We also host **visiting students** and **research interns**. These positions are ideal for students who wish to explore research topics in optimization and AI for Science before pursuing graduate studies.

To apply, please send:
- A short CV  
- Transcript  
- Proposed research period and topic of interest  

---

## 💡 Tips for Applicants

- Familiarize yourself with our **recent publications** on [Publications](/publications/).  
- In your email, briefly describe why your interests align with our ongoing projects.  
- Early contact (before formal deadlines) is encouraged — it helps identify the best matching funding channel.

